## Key Findings

### 1. Notability Files (.note) - 92% of collection
- **Format:** ZIP archive containing binary plist + embedded PDFs/images
- **Content type:** Primarily HANDWRITTEN notes (not typed text)
- **Challenge:** Handwriting stored as drawing vectors, not extractable text
- **Solution:** Extract embedded PDFs and images; OCR if text needed

### 2. Massive Duplication Problem
| Category | Count | Notes |
|----------|-------|-------|
| Byte-identical duplicates | 60 groups | Safe to auto-dedupe |
| Version variants (different content) | 281 groups | Need careful comparison |
| Total duplicate files | 1,647+ | ~66% of collection |

**Critical:** The "(2)" version sometimes has MORE content than the original.

### 3. OneNote Files (.one) - 145 files
- Backup structure with dated versions
- Located in `Backup\16.0\Backup\` folders
- Can extract text using pyOneNote library

